MadMoo


   "Come on, move to the left."  MadMoo wispers to himself.  He was aiming 
his Sniper rifle at the crowd of a maximals.  He was there to assinate the 
President of Macrosoft.  The Presidents Name was Bill Setag(Gates 
Backwards).

   Just Then Mr. Setag move to the left.  MadMoo looked through the Scope 
one last time and fired.  Setag Robotic Head Flew off as he fell to the 
ground, his Spark Failing him.

   The Crowd ran around wild with the resent assination.  MadMoo got up from 
his place in the catwalks and ran for the exit.  When he open the Exit door, 
he noticed about 5 Cop Cars just pulling up outside.

   "That Son of a Rust Picket set me up."  MadMoo said to himself as he ran 
in he other direction.

   He open an other door seeing police coming up a staircase.  The lead 
police Officer told him not to move.  MadMoo took out a smoke Gernade and 
threw it at the officers.

   "Get Down, its a Gernade."  The lead police officer yelled as his sqradon 
ducked down covering their heads.

   MadMoo closed the door.  He found a Metal Rod and slamed it in the door 
handle, making it impossile to open.

   MadMoo looked around where he was and noticed he was in a storage area.  
He grabbed a rope, blanket, and a Computer Printer.  He tied the Rope around 
the Computer Printer.  With the blanket he folded it up and put it in one of 
his storage pit.

   "Hmm, If I hold the Gernade for 2.3562 secounds then throw it the hole 
should be big enough."  MadMoo says as he takes out a gernade.  He pulls the 
pin.  Excatly 2.3562 seconds after he pulled the pin, he threw it at the 
roof.  Right as the very tip of the gernade hit the roof, it went off.  
There was a 11 foot hole(In Radius) in the metalic roof.

   MadMoo took the Printer and threw it up at the hole.  It landed on the 
roof.  MadMoo then grabbed the rope and climb up it.  Somehow the printer 
held and he made it to the roof.  He then ran to the edge and jumped.  He 
quickly wiped out the blanket and used it as a Parachute.  He made it 
Saftley on the ground.
